Program: Discovery
Title: The great extinction debate
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwdq
Last Broadcast Date: 20 March 1995
Are we over thinking the extinction of the dinosaurs? Theories about the demise of the dinosaurs may not be needed, according to one evolution expert. Also in the programme the search for extra terrestrial life, how technology is picking up tell tale signs of industrial pollution in sea shells, and the prospects for transplanting pigs' organs into human patients. Show less